obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (29953)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297&sectionId=29953&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Limitation Act, 1963.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 31-`
  line `10- 2019).`
  line
  line `2. 1st January, 1964, vide notification No. S.O. 3118, dated 29th October, 1963, see Gazette of India, Part II, sec. 3 (ii).`
  line `Amended in West Bengal by W.B. Act 18 of 1977.`
  line
  line `1st September, 1984, vide notification No. S.O. 647(C), in respect of the State of Sikkim dated 24th August, 1984, see`
  line `Gazette of India, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (29954)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297&sectionId=29954&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "applicant" includes--`
  line
  line `(i) a petitioner;`
  line
  line `(ii) any person from or through whom an applicant derives his right to apply;`
  line
  line `(iii) any person whose estate is represented by the applicant as executor, administrator or`
  line `other representative;`
  line
  line `(b) "application" includes a petition;`
  line
  line `(c) "bill of exchange" includes a hundi and a cheque;`
  line
  line `(d) "bond" includes any instrument whereby a person obliges himself to pay money to another,`
  line `on condition that the obligation shall be void if a specified act is performed, or is not performed, as`
  line `the case may be;`
  line
  line `(e) "defendant" includes--`
  line
  line `(i) any person from or through whom a defendant derives his liability to be sued;`
  line
  line `(ii) any person whose estate is represented by the defendant as executor, administrator or`
  line `other representative;`
  line
  line `(f) "easement" includes a right not arising from contract, by which one person is entitled to`
  line `remove and appropriate for his own profit any part of the soil belonging to another or anything`
  line `growing in, or attached to, or subsisting upon, the land of another;`
  line
  line `(g) "foreign country" means any country other than India;`
  line
  line `(h) "good faith"--nothing shall be deemed to be done in good faith which is not done with due`
  line `care and attention;`
  line
  line `(i) "plaintiff" includes--`
  line
  line `(i) any person from or through whom a plaintiff derives his right to sue;`
  line
  line `(ii) any person whose estate is represented by the plaintiff as executor, administrator or other`
  line representative;
  line
  line `(j) "period of limitation" means the period of limitation prescribed for any suit, appeal or`
  line `application by the Schedule, and "prescribed period" means the period of limitation computed in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(k) "promissory note" means any instrument whereby the maker engages absolutely to pay a`
  line `specified sum of money to another at a time therein limited, or on demand, or at sight;`
  line
  line `(l) "suit" does not include an appeal or an application;`
  line
  line `(m) "tort" means a civil wrong which is not exclusively the breach of a contract or the breach of a`
  line trust;
  line
  line `(n) "trustee" does not include a benamidar, a mortgagee remaining in possession after the`
  line `mortgage has been satisfied or a person in wrongful possession without title.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (29955)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Bar of limitation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297&sectionId=29955&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions contained in sections 4 to 24 (inclusive), every`
  line `suit instituted, appeal preferred, and application made after the prescribed period shall be dismissed,`
  line `although limitation has not been set up as a defence.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) a suit is instituted,--`
  line
  line `(i) in an ordinary case, when the plaint is presented to the proper officer;`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of a pauper, when his application for leave to sue as a pauper is made; and`
  line
  line `(iii) in the case of a claim against a company which is being wound up by the court, when the`
  line `claimant first sends in his claim to the official liquidator;`
  line
  line `(b) any claim by way of a set off or a counter claim, shall be treated as a separate suit and shall be`
  line `deemed to have been instituted--`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of a set off, on the same date as the suit in which the set off is pleaded;`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of a counter claim, on the date on which the counter claim is made in court;`
  line
  line `(c) an application by notice of motion in a High Court is made when the application is presented`
  line `to the proper officer of that court.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (29956)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Expiry of prescribed period when court is closed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297&sectionId=29956&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Where the prescribed period for any suit,`
  line `appeal or application expires on a day when the court is closed, the suit, appeal or application may be`
  line `instituted, preferred or made on the day when the court re-opens.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--A court shall be deemed to be closed on any day within the meaning of this section if`
  line `during any part of its normal working hours it remains closed on that day.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (29957)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Extension of prescribed period in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297&sectionId=29957&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Any appeal or any application, other than an`
  line `application under any of the provisions of Order XXI of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908),`
  line `may be admitted after the prescribed period if the appellant or the applicant satisfies the court that he had`
  line `sufficient cause for not preferring the appeal or making the application within such period.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--The fact that the appellant or the applicant was misled by any order, practice or`
  line `judgment of the High Court in ascertaining or computing the prescribed period may be sufficient cause`
  line `within the meaning of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (29958)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Legal disability.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297&sectionId=29958&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a person entitled to institute a suit or make an application for the`
  line `execution of a decree is, at the time from which the prescribed period is to be reckoned, a minor or insane,`
  line `or an idiot, he may institute the suit or make the application within the same period after the disability has`
  line `ceased, as would otherwise have been allowed from the time specified therefor in the third column of the`
  line Schedule.
  line
  line `(2) Where such person is, at the time from which the prescribed period is to be reckoned, affected by`
  line `two such disabilities, or where, before his disability has ceased, he is affected by another disability, he`
  line `may institute the suit or make the application within the same period after both disabilities have ceased, as`
  line `would otherwise have been allowed from the time so specified.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the disability continues up to the death of that person, his legal representative may institute`
  line `the suit or make the application within the same period after the death, as would otherwise have been`
  line `allowed from the time so specified.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the legal representative referred to in sub-section (3) is, at the date of the death of the`
  line `person whom he represents, affected by any such disability, the rules contained in sub-sections (1) and (2)`
  line `shall apply.`
  line
  line `(5) Where a person under disability dies after the disability ceases but within the period allowed to`
  line `him under this section, his legal representative may institute the suit or make the application within the`
  line `same period after the death, as would otherwise have been available to that person had he not died.`
  line
  line `Explanation.For the purposes of this section, "minor" includes a child in the womb.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (29959)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Disability of one of several persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297&sectionId=29959&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Where one of several persons jointly entitled to institute a`
  line `suit or make an application for the execution of a decree is under any such disability, and a discharge can`
  line `be given without the concurrence of such person, time will run against them all; but, where no such`
  line `discharge can be given, time will not run as against any of them until one of them becomes capable of`
  line `giving such discharge without the concurrence of the others or until the disability has ceased.`
  line
  line `Explanation I.—This section applies to a discharge from every kind of liability, including a liability`
  line `in respect of any immovable property.`
  line
  line `Explanation II.—For the purposes of this section, the Manager of a Hindu undivided family governed`
  line `by the Mitakshara law shall be deemed to be capable of giving a discharge without the concurrence of the`
  line `other members of the family only if he is in management of the joint family property.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (29960)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Special exceptions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297&sectionId=29960&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in section 6 or in section 7 applies to suits to enforce rights of`
  line `pre-emption, or shall be deemed to extend, for more than three years from the cessation of the disability`
  line `or the death of the person affected thereby, the period of limitation for any suit or application.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (29961)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Continuous running of time.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297&sectionId=29961&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Where once time has begun to run, no subsequent disability or`
  line `inability to institute a suit or make an application stops it:`
  line
  line `Provided that, where letters of administration to the estate of a creditor have been granted to his`
  line `debtor, the running of the period of limitation for a suit to recover the debt shall be suspended while the`
  line `administration continues.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (29962)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Suits against trustees and their representatives.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297&sectionId=29962&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the`
  line `foregoing provisions of this Act, no suit against a person in whom property has become vested in trust for`
  line `any specific purpose, or against his legal representatives or assigns (not being assigns for valuable`
  line `consideration), for the purpose of following in his or their hands such property, or the proceeds thereof, or`
  line `for an account of such property or proceeds, shall be barred by any length of time.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section any property comprised in a Hindu, Muslim or`
  line `Buddhist religious or charitable endowment shall be deemed to be property vested in trust for a specific`
  line `purpose and the manager of the property shall be deemed to be the trustee thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (29963)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Suits on contracts entered into outside the territories to which the Act extends.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297&sectionId=29963&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Suits`
  line `instituted in the territories to which this Act extends on contracts entered into in the State of Jammu and`
  line `Kashmir or in a foreign country shall be subject to the rules of limitation contained in this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) No rule of limitation in force in the State of Jammu and Kashmir or in a foreign country shall be a`
  line `defence to a suit instituted in the said territories on a contract entered into in that State on in a foreign`
  line `country unless—`
  line
  line `(a) the rule has extinguished the contract; and`
  line
  line `(b) the parties were domiciled in that State or in the foreign country during the period prescribed`
  line `by such rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (29964)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Exclusion of time in legal proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes `2. The words "on which the decree or order is founded" omitted by Act 46 of 1999, s. 33 (w.e.f. 1-7-2002).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297&sectionId=29964&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) In computing the period of limitation for any suit,`
  line `appeal or application, the day from which such period is to be reckoned, shall be excluded.`
  line
  line `(2) In computing the period of limitation for an appeal or an application for leave to appeal or for`
  line `revision or for review of a judgment, the day on which the judgment complained of was pronounced and`
  line `the time requisite for obtaining a copy of the decree, sentence or order appealed from or sought to be`
  line `revised or reviewed shall be excluded.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a decree or order is appealed from or sought to be revised or reviewed, or where an`
  line `application is made for leave to appeal from a decree or order, the time requisite for obtaining a copy of`
  line `the judgment ^2`
  line `*** shall also be excluded.`
  line
  line `(4) In computing the period of limitation for an application to set aside an award, the time requisite`
  line `for obtaining a copy of the award shall be excluded.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In computing under this section the time requisite for obtaining a copy of a decree or`
  line `an order, any time taken by the court to prepare the decree or order before an application for a copy`
  line `thereof is made shall not be excluded.`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (29965)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Exclusion of time in cases where leave to sue or appeal as a pauper is applied for.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297&sectionId=29965&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line In
  line `computing the period of limitation prescribed for any suit or appeal in any case where an application for`
  line `leave to sue or appeal as a pauper has been made and rejected, the time during which the applicant has`
  line `been prosecuting in good faith his application for such leave shall be excluded, and the court may, on`
  line `payment of the court fees prescribed for such suit or appeal, treat the suit or appeal as having the same`
  line `force and effect as if the court fees had been paid in the first instance.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (29966)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Exclusion of time of proceeding bona fide in court without jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297&sectionId=29966&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) In computing the`
  line `period of limitation for any suit the time during which the plaintiff has been prosecuting with due`
  line `diligence another civil proceeding, whether in a court of first instance or of appeal or revision, against the`
  line `defendant shall be excluded, where the proceeding relates to the same matter in issue and is prosecuted in`
  line `good faith in a court which, from defect of jurisdiction or other cause of a like nature, is unable to`
  line `entertain it.`
  line
  line `(2) In computing the period of limitation for any application, the time during which the applicant has`
  line `been prosecuting with due diligence another civil proceeding, whether in a court of first instance or of`
  line `appeal or revision, against the same party for the same relief shall be excluded, where such proceeding is`
  line `prosecuted in good faith in a court which, from defect of jurisdiction or other cause of a like nature, is`
  line `unable to entertain it.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in rule 2 of Order XXIII of the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), the provisions of sub-section (1) shall apply in relation to a fresh suit`
  line `instituted on permission granted by the court under rule 1 of that Order, where such permission is granted`
  line `on the ground that the first suit must fail by reason of a defect in the jurisdiction of the court or other`
  line `cause of a like nature.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section,—`
  line
  line `(a) in excluding the time during which a former civil proceeding was pending, the day on which`
  line `that proceeding was instituted and the day on which it ended shall both be counted;`
  line
  line `(b) a plaintiff or an applicant resisting an appeal shall be deemed to be prosecuting a proceeding;`
  line
  line `(c) misjoinder of parties or of causes of action shall be deemed to be a cause of a like nature with`
  line `defect of jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (29967)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Exclusion of time in certain other cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297&sectionId=29967&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) In computing the period of limitation of any suit`
  line `or application for the execution of a decree, the institution or execution of which has been stayed by`
  line `injunction or order, the time of the continuance of the injunction or order, the day on which it was issued`
  line `or made, and the day on which it was withdrawn, shall be excluded.`
  line
  line `(2) In computing the period of limitation for any suit of which notice has been given, or for which the`
  line `previous consent or sanction of the Government or any other authority is required, in accordance with the`
  line `requirements of any law for the time being in force, the period of such notice or, as the case may be, the`
  line `time required for obtaining such consent or sanction shall be excluded.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In excluding the time required for obtaining the consent or sanction of the`
  line `Government or any other authority, the date on which the application was made for obtaining the consent`
  line `or sanction and the date of receipt of the order of the Government or other authority shall both be`
  line counted.
  line
  line `(3) In computing the period of limitation for any suit or application for execution of a decree by any`
  line `receiver or interim receiver appointed in proceedings for the adjudication of a person as an insolvent or by`
  line `any liquidator or provisional liquidator appointed in proceedings for the winding up of a company, the`
  line `period beginning with the date of institution of such proceeding and ending with the expiry of three`
  line `months from the date of appointment of such receiver or liquidator, as the case may be, shall be excluded.`
  line
  line `(4) In computing the period of limitation for a suit for possession by a purchaser at a sale in execution`
  line `of a decree, the time during which a proceeding to set aside the sale has been prosecuted shall be`
  line excluded.
  line
  line `(5) In computing the period of limitation for any suit the time during which the defendant has been`
  line `absent from India and from the territories outside India under the administration of the Central`
  line `Government, shall be excluded.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (29968)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Effect of death on or before the accrual of the right to sue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297&sectionId=29968&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a person who would, if`
  line `he were living, have a right to institute a suit or make an application dies before the right accrues, or`
  line `where a right to institute a suit or make an application accrues only on the death of a person, the period of`
  line `limitation shall be computed from the time when there is a legal representative of the deceased capable of`
  line `instituting such suit or making such application.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a person against whom, if he were living, a right to institute a suit or make an application`
  line `would have accrued dies before the right accrues, or where a right to institute a suit or make an`
  line `application against any person accrues on the death of such person, the period of limitation shall be`
  line `computed from the time when there is a legal representative of the deceased against whom the plaintiff`
  line `may institute such suit or make such application.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) applies to suits to enforce rights of pre-emption or to`
  line `suits for the possession of immovable property or of a hereditary office.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (29969)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Effect of fraud or mistake.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297&sectionId=29969&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, in the case of any suit or application for which a period`
  line `of limitation is prescribed by this Act,—`
  line
  line `(a) the suit or application is based upon the fraud of the defendant or respondent or his agent; or`
  line
  line `(b) the knowledge of the right or title on which a suit or application is founded is concealed by`
  line `the fraud of any such person as aforesaid; or`
  line
  line `(c) the suit or application is for relief from the consequences of a mistake; or`
  line
  line `(d) where any document necessary to establish the right of the plaintiff or applicant has been`
  line `fraudulently concealed from him,`
  line
  line `the period of limitation shall not begin to run until the plaintiff or applicant has discovered the fraud or`
  line `the mistake or could, with reasonable diligence, have discovered it; or in the case of a concealed`
  line `document, until the plaintiff or the applicant first had the means of producing the concealed document or`
  line `compelling its production:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall enable any suit to be instituted or application to be made to`
  line `recover or enforce any charge against, or set aside any transaction affecting, any property which—`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of fraud, has been purchased for valuable consideration by a person who was not a`
  line `party to the fraud and did not at the time of the purchase know, or have reason to believe, that any`
  line `fraud had been committed, or`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of mistake, has been purchased for valuable consideration subsequently to the`
  line `transaction in which the mistake was made, by a person who did not know, or have reason to believe,`
  line `that the mistake had been made, or`
  line
  line `(iii) in the case of a concealed document, has been purchased for valuable consideration by a`
  line `person who was not a party to the concealment and, did not at the time of purchase know, or have`
  line `reason to believe, that the document had been concealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a judgment-debtor has, by fraud or force, prevented the execution of a decree or order`
  line `within the period of limitation, the court may, on the application of the judgment-creditor made after the`
  line `expiry of the said period extend the period for execution of the decree or order:`
  line
  line `Provided that such application is made within one year from the date of the discovery of the fraud or`
  line `the cessation of force, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (29970)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Effect of acknowledgment in writing.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297&sectionId=29970&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, before the expiration of the prescribed`
  line `period for a suit or application in respect of any property or right, an acknowledgment of liability in`
  line `respect of such property or right has been made in writing signed by the party against whom such`
  line `property or right is claimed, or by any person through whom he derives his title or liability, a fresh period`
  line `of limitation shall be computed from the time when the acknowledgment was so signed.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the writing containing the acknowledgment is undated, oral evidence may be given of the`
  line `time when it was signed; but subject to the provisions of the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872), oral`
  line `evidence of its contents shall not be received.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section,—`
  line
  line `(a) an acknowledgment may be sufficient though it omits to specify the exact nature of the`
  line `property or right, or avers that the time for payment, delivery, performance or enjoyment has not yet`
  line `come or is accompanied by a refusal to pay, deliver, perform or permit to enjoy, or is coupled with a`
  line `claim to set off, or is addressed to a person other than a person entitled to the property or right,`
  line
  line `(b) the word "signed" means signed either personally or by an agent duly authorised in this`
  line `behalf, and`
  line
  line `(c) an application for the execution of a decree or order shall not be deemed to be an application`
  line `in respect of any property or right.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (29971)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Effect of payment on account of debt or of interest on legacy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297&sectionId=29971&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Where payment on account of`
  line `a debt or of interest on a legacy is made before the expiration of the prescribed period by the person liable`
  line `to pay the debt or legacy or by his agent duly authorised in this behalf, a fresh period of limitation shall be`
  line `computed from the time when the payment was made:`
  line
  line `Provided that, save in the case of payment of interest made before the 1st day of January, 1928, an`
  line `acknowledgment of the payment appears in the handwriting of, or in a writing signed by, the person`
  line `making the payment.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section,—`
  line
  line `(a) where mortgaged land is in the possession of the mortgagee, the receipt of the rent or produce`
  line `of such land shall be deemed to be a payment;`
  line
  line `(b) "debt" does not include money payable under a decree or order of a court.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (29972)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Effect of acknowledgment or payment by another person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297&sectionId=29972&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The expression "agent duly`
  line `authorised in this behalf" in sections 18 and 19 shall, in the case of a person under disability, include his`
  line `lawful guardian, committee or manager or an agent duly authorised by such guardian, committee or`
  line `manager to sign the acknowledgment or make the payment.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in the said sections renders one of several joint contractors, partners, executors or`
  line `mortgagees chargeable by reason only of a written acknowledgment signed by, or of a payment made by,`
  line `or by the agent of, any other or others of them.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of the said sections,—`
  line
  line `(a) an acknowledgment signed or a payment made in respect of any liability by, or by the duly`
  line `authorised agent of, any limited owner of property who is governed by Hindu law, shall be a`
  line `valid acknowledgment or payment, as the case may be, against a reversioner succeeding to such`
  line `liability; and`
  line
  line `(b) where a liability has been incurred by, or on behalf of a Hindu undivided family as such, an`
  line `acknowledgment or payment made by, or by the duly authorised agent of, the manager of the family`
  line `for the time being shall be deemed to have been made on behalf of the whole family.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (29973)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Effect of substituting or adding new plaintiff or defendant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297&sectionId=29973&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where after the institution of`
  line `a suit, a new plaintiff or defendant is substituted or added, the suit shall, as regards him, be deemed to`
  line `have been instituted when he was so made a party:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the court is satisfied that the omission to include a new plaintiff or defendant was`
  line `due to a mistake made in good faith it may direct that the suit as regards such plaintiff or defendant shall`
  line `be deemed to have been instituted on any earlier date.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall apply to a case where a party is added or substituted owing to`
  line `assignment or devolution of any interest during the pendency of a suit or where a plaintiff is made a`
  line `defendant or a defendant is made a plaintiff.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (29974)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Continuing breaches and torts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297&sectionId=29974&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `In the case of a continuing breach of contract or in the case of`
  line `a continuing tort, a fresh period of limitation begins to run at every moment of the time during which the`
  line `breach or the tort, as the case may be, continues.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (29975)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Suits for compensation for acts not actionable without special damage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297&sectionId=29975&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `In the case of a suit`
  line `for compensation for an act which does not give rise to a cause of action unless some specific injury`
  line `actually results therefrom, the period of limitation shall be computed from the time when the injury`
  line results.
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (29976)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Computation of time mentioned in instruments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297&sectionId=29976&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `All instruments shall for the purposes of this`
  line `Act be deemed to be made with reference to the Gregorian calendar.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (29977)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Acquisition of easements by prescription.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297&sectionId=29977&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the access and use of light or air to and`
  line `for any building have been peaceably enjoyed therewith as an easement, and as of right, without`
  line `interruption, and for twenty years, and where any way or watercourse or the use of any water or any other`
  line `easement (whether affirmative or negative) has been peaceably and openly enjoyed by any person`
  line `claiming title thereto as an easement and as of right without interruption and for twenty years, the right to`
  line `such access and use of light or air, way, watercourse, use of water, or other easement shall be absolute`
  line `and indefeasible.`
  line
  line `(2) Each of the said periods of twenty years shall be taken to be a period ending within two years next`
  line `before the institution of the suit wherein the claim to which such period relates is contested.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the property over which a right is claimed under sub-section (1) belongs to the`
  line `Government that sub-section shall be read as if for the words "twenty years" the words "thirty years"`
  line `were substituted.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—Nothing is an interruption within the meaning of this section, unless where there is an`
  line `actual discontinuance of the possession or enjoyment by reason of an obstruction by the act of some`
  line `person other than the claimant, and unless such obstruction is submitted to or acquiesced in for one year`
  line `after the claimant has notice thereof and of the person making or authorising the same to be made.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (29978)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Exclusion in favour of reversioner of servient tenement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297&sectionId=29978&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Where any land or water upon, over`
  line `or from, which any easement has been enjoyed or derived has been held under or by virtue of any interest`
  line `for life or in terms of years exceeding three years from the granting thereof, the time of the enjoyment of`
  line `such easement during the continuance of such interest or term shall be excluded in the computation of the`
  line `period twenty years in case the claim is, within three years next after the determination of such interest or`
  line `term resisted by the person entitled on such determination to the said land or water.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (29979)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Extinguishment of right to property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297&sectionId=29979&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `At the determination of the period hereby limited to any`
  line `person for instituting a suit for possession of any property, his right to such property shall be`
  line extinguished.
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (29980)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title Repealed.
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297&sectionId=29980&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `[Amendment of certain Acts.]— Rep. by Repealing and Amending Act, 1974 (56 of 1974), s. 2 and`
  line `the First Schedule (w.e.f. 20-12-1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (29984)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title Savings
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297&sectionId=29984&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) Nothing in this Act shall affect section 25 of the Indian Contract`
  line `Act, 1872 (9 of 1872).`
  line
  line `(2) Where any special or local law prescribes for any suit, appeal or application a period of limitation`
  line `different from the period prescribed by the Schedule, the provisions of section 3 shall apply as if such`
  line `period were the period prescribed by the Schedule and for the purpose of determining any period of`
  line `limitation prescribed for any suit, appeal or application by any special or local law, the provisions`
  line `contained in sections 4 to 24 (inclusive) shall apply only in so far as, and to the extent to which, they are`
  line `not expressly excluded by such special or local law.`
  line
  line `(3) Save as otherwise provided in any law for the time being in force with respect to marriage and`
  line `divorce, nothing in this Act shall apply to any suit or other proceeding under any such law.`
  line
  line `(4) Sections 25 and 26 and the definition of "easement" in section 2 shall not apply to cases arising in`
  line `the territories to which the Indian Easements Act, 1882 (5 of 1882), may for the time being extend.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (29985)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Provision for suits, etc., for which the prescribed period is shorter than the period prescribed by the Indian Limitation Act, 1908`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297&sectionId=29985&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) any suit for which the period of limitation is shorter than the period of limitation prescribed by`
  line `the Indian Limitation Act, 1908 (9 of 1908), may be instituted within a period of ^1`
  line `[seven years next]`
  line `after the commencement of this Act or within the period prescribed for such suit by the Indian`
  line `Limitation Act, 1908 (9 of 1908), whichever period expires earlier:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that if in respect of any such suit, the said period of seven years expires earlier than`
  line `the period of limitation prescribed therefor under the Indian Limitation Act, 1908 (9 of 1908) and the`
  line `said period of seven years together with so much of the period of limitation in respect of such suit`
  line `under the Indian Limitation Act, 1908 (9 of 1908), as has already expired before the commencement`
  line `of this Act is shorter than the period prescribed for such suit under this Act, then, the suit may be`
  line `instituted within the period of limitation prescribed therefor under this Act;]`
  line
  line `(b) any appeal or application for which the period of limitation is shorter than the period of`
  line `limitation prescribed by the Indian Limitation Act, 1908 (9 of 1908), may be preferred or made within`
  line `a period of ninety days next after the commencement of this Act or within the period prescribed for`
  line `such appeal or application by the Indian Limitation Act, 1908, whichever period expires earlier.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh (UTs).--`
  line
  line `Insertion of Section 30A .-- After section 30, insert the following section, namely: --`
  line
  line `"30A. Provision for suits, etc., for which the prescribed period is shorter than the period prescribed by the Limitation Act, samvat 1995.--Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) Any suit for which the period of limitation is shorter than the period of limitation prescribed by the Limitation Act, Samvat 1995, may be instituted within a period of one year next after the commencement of the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganisation Act, 2019 or within the period prescribed for such suit by the Limitation Act, Samvat 1995, whichever period expires earlier:`
  line
  line `Provided that if in respect of any such suit, the said period of one year expires earlier than period of limitation prescribed therefor under the Limitation Act, Samvat 1995 (now repealed) and the said period of one year together with so much of the period of limitation in respect of such suit under the said Act, as has already expired before the commencement of the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganisation Act, 2019 is shorter than the period prescribed for such suit under the Limitation Act, 1963, then, the suit may be instituted within the period of limitation prescribed therefor under the Limitation Act, 1963;`
  line
  line `(b) Any appeal or application for which the period of limitation is shorter than the period of limitation prescribed by the Limitation Act, Samvat 1995, may be preferred or made within a period of ninety days next after the commencement of the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganisation Act, 2019 or within the period prescribed for such appeal or application by the Limitation Act, Samvat 1995, whichever period expires earlier."`
  line
  line `[Vide the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, vide notification No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O. 3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 1969, s. 2, for "five years" (w.e.f. 26-3-1969).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 26-3-1969).`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (29986)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Provisions as to barred or pending suits, etc`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297&sectionId=29986&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00005_196336_1517807319297
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act shall,—`
  line
  line `(a) enable any suit, appeal or application to be instituted, preferred or made, for which the period`
  line `of limitation prescribed by the Indian Limitation Act, 1908 (9 of 1908), expired before the`
  line `commencement of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) affect any suit, appeal or application instituted, preferred or made before, and pending at, such`
  line commencement.
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
